description:
Phillip Jacobson is a graduate of the Savannah College of Art and Design. He completed his MFA in 2013, and currently lives in Savannah, GA working as a freelance artist. His pre-graduate work includes the Game Over Kicsktarter anthology and the self-published comic series Pancakes for Yeti.

Phillip began working on the Uglydolls graphic novel series in 2012. Co-illustrated by Ian McGinty, the series ran for four volumes and includes short stories by various guest artists. In 2013, he was contracted by Boom! Studios to work as the Cover A artist for the Regular Show comic series. He has also done two short stories for Adventure Time.

Recently, Phillip was hired by Nickelodeon to work on the upcoming series Pig Goat Banana Cricket, created by Dave Cooper and Johnny Ryan.
name: Phil Jacobson
